INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("120", "1", "2014-04-29 01:42:28", "2014-04-29 01:42:28", "<b>General</b>\r\n\r\nBy using the sweetbabylilly.com.au website (“Site”) you agree to be bound by the terms and conditions set out below (“Terms and Conditions”).\r\n\r\nThe words “we”, “us”, “our” and “Sweet Baby Lilly” mean Sweet Baby Lilly ABN 84501284399 (and its directors, officers, employees, agents, shareholders or related entities) of PO Box 64, Rozelle NSW 2039 and the words “you” and “your” refer to the users of this website including our customers and members.\r\n\r\nOur Privacy Policy and Delivery &amp; Return Policy located on the Site form part of these Terms and Conditions.  By using the Site, you acknowledge and agree to our Privacy Policy and Delivery &amp; Return Policy.\r\n\r\nWe make no warranty or representation as to the suitability of the Site or our products and services for any purpose.  By using the Site, you warrant that you have satisfied yourself as to its suitability for your purpose.\r\n\r\nThe material contained on the Site is intended for use in Australia only.\r\n\r\nWe may change these Terms and Conditions (including our Privacy Policy and Delivery &amp; Return Policy) at any time, and such modifications will be effective as soon as they are posted on the Site.  By continuing to use the Site after these Terms and Conditions have been modified, you agree to be bound by the changes.  If you have an order that has been accepted by us, the Terms and Conditions that will apply to the order are the Terms and Conditions that applied at the time you placed your order.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Acceptance of Terms and Conditions</b>\r\n\r\nYou should read and familiarise yourself with these Terms and Conditions before you use the Site.  By using the Site, you expressly agree to these Terms and Conditions as they are amended from time to time and you acknowledge that you have read and understood them.\r\n\r\nYou should always check these Terms and Conditions prior to using the Site to make sure that you have a current understanding of the Terms and Conditions.    You should discontinue use of the Site if you do not agree with our Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\nBy using this Site, you acknowledge that you are over the age of 18 years.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Disclaimer and Limitation of Liability</b>\r\n\r\nTo the best of our knowledge, the information on our website is accurate, current and complete, however, we do not make any representation or warranty as to the accuracy, currency or completeness of the information or any information provided by third parties. If your product is unavailable, we will contact you to advise you. Although we aim to ensure information on our Site is correct, we reserve the right to correct information provided on the Site if found to be incorrect.  You should exercise and use your own discretion and judgement when purchasing a product.\r\n\r\nThe law implies certain terms, conditions, warranties or guarantees (“prescribed terms”) in relation to the supply of goods and services and nothing in these Terms and Conditions excludes or restricts or modifies any prescribed terms which, pursuant to the Australian Consumer Law (or other relevant legislation), cannot be excluded or modified. However, to the extent permitted by law we limit our liability to, at our option:\r\n\r\n(1)                  the cost of replacing the goods or supplying equivalent goods; or\r\n\r\n(2)                  the cost of repair of the goods; or\r\n\r\n(3)                  the cost of having the goods repaired or replaced.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe exclude all other implied terms and warranties whether statutory or otherwise, relating to your use of this website or our products and services.\r\n\r\nYou shall indemnify and keep us indemnified in respect of all claims and demands against us arising out of, in connection with, or relating to any loss, injury, expense or damage arising howsoever in relation to goods sold by us to you. In no event shall we be liable for any claims or damages including, but not limited to, claims for faulty design, negligent or misleading advice, damages arising from loss or use of the products, and any indirect, special or consequential damages or injury to any person or entity.\r\n\r\nIf we become liable to you for loss or damage of any kind arising out of these Terms and Conditions, your use of the Site or in connection with the relationship established by it, our liability is reduced to the extent (if any) that you cause or contribute to the loss or damage. This applies whether our liability is in contract, tort (including negligence), under any law or otherwise.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Prices</b>\r\n\r\nAll prices quoted on our Site are in Australian dollars (AUD).  We endeavour to ensure that our price list is current and reserve the right to amend our prices at any time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Payment Security</b>\r\n\r\nWe have taken every possible measure to ensure that you can purchase online with complete confidence.\r\n\r\nWe have a secure transaction system which uses 128 bit Secure Sockets Layer technology (SSL) to ensure your online shopping experience is safe and secure at all times.  SSL is the industry standard for encryption technology.\r\n\r\nIf you are concerned about using your credit/debit card online, you can contact us for more information or assistance.\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Use and Intellectual Property Rights</b>\r\n\r\nYou may use the Site and the information contained within it for your own personal and non-commercial use only.\r\n\r\nThe information and material contained within this Site (including images, illustrations, graphics, designs, photographs, icons, logos and written materials) are copyright, trademarks and other intellectual property owned or licensed by Sweet Baby Lilly. You may make any copies of any information reasonably incidental to your viewing of the Site and may retain a single permanent copy for your personal reference. The information may not otherwise be used, copied, reproduced, published, stored in a retrieval system, altered, transmitted in any form or by any means in whole or in part (except where by law such use cannot be prohibited) without our prior written approval.\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Product Information</b>\r\n\r\nProducts displayed on the Site may be available in selected stores throughout Australia.  In some cases, products displayed for sale on the Site may not be available in all stores.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Design Protection</b>\r\n\r\nNo rights in the design of our products, or designs incorporated in our products, will pass to you because of your purchase of our products.  You agree not to copy or reproduce, or cause to be copied or reproduced, either directly or indirectly, our products, product designs, designs incorporated in our products, or product packaging.  This provision will survive termination of these Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Colours</b>\r\n\r\nWe have made every effort to display the colours of our products that appear on the Site as accurately as possible.  Because the actual colours you see will depend on your monitor, we cannot guarantee that your monitor’s display of any colour will be accurate.\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Force Majeure</b>\r\n\r\nIf by reason of any fact, circumstance, matter or thing beyond our reasonable control we are unable to perform in whole or in part any obligation to you we are relieved of that obligation to the extent and for the period that we are so unable to perform and we are not liable to you in respect of such inability.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>External Websites and Third Party Trademarks</b>\r\n\r\nThis website may contain links to external websites that are not operated by us.  We make no representations or warranties about those external websites and have no responsibility or liability for them.  You agree that your access to, and use of, them is at your risk absolutely.\r\n\r\nThird party trademarks, trade names, product names and logos contained on the Site may be trademarks of their respective owners.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Severability</b>\r\n\r\nIf any provision of these Terms and Conditions is found to be void or unenforceable at law, that provision will not affect any other provision of these Terms and Conditions and, as far as is possible, will be read down to the extent required to make it enforceable.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Governing Law</b>\r\n\r\nThese Terms and Conditions are governed by the law in force in the State of New South Wales, Australia.", "Terms and Conditions of Use", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "terms-and-conditions", "", "", "2014-06-06 05:07:21", "2014-06-06 05:07:21", "", "0", "http://sweetbabylilly.com.au/?page_id=120", "0", "page", "", "0");
