INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("363", "1", "2015-06-10 04:56:27", "2015-06-10 04:56:27", "<p dir=\"ltr\">There is nothing sweeter than a sleeping baby, but sometimes it may seem like all your baby wants to do is anything but sleep. Is your baby not sleeping ? According to the Australian Centre for Education in Sleep ( ACES), an Australian organisation founded to increase awareness about the importance of sleep and what happens when we don\'t get enough sleep, babies under 1 need  14-18 hours of sleep throughout the day and night. Healthy baby sleep is crucial to your baby’s brain development and decreases chances of general health problems and emotional difficulties like depression and anxiety later in life. Is your baby keeping you up all night, here some good tips to give your baby and you, your sleep back.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Routine. Having a routine before bed cues your baby that it is time to transition to bedtime. Keep a consistent bed time every night.  You can start a routine with a bath and story before bed.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Naps. Babies sleep better at night when they are taking consistent naps during the day. If a baby is too tired this in turn came make the transition to sleep even more difficult.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Environment. Create the best environment that is conducive to sleep for your baby.Make sure that the room is dark enough and is a comfortable sleeping environment. You can add a sound machine or a fan. White noise can help drown out other noises especially if you have other children who are older that like to run around.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Be Active During the Day. Keep your baby active and stimulated when they are awake. This will help them go down faster and longer. Take time to play with your baby. Not only does it help with their sleep but helps with the development as well.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Don’t put baby down with bottle. When establishing bedtime routines it is not good to put baby down with a last bottle. You may be thinking that they may sleep longer because they won’t wake up hungry but in turn they will probably wake up wanting their diaper changed.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Don’t bring baby in your bed. Both baby and you sleep better when you are in your own beds. It also helps with their separation anxiety and it is safer for baby to sleep alone.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Help Ease the Transition. When you put your baby to bed, stay with them for 10-15 minutes before leaving the room. This helps them transition better and helps get them more familiar with their surroundings before bed</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you are breastfeeding stop drinking caffeine. Caffeine from soda and coffee can turn up in your breast milk and it can be enough to affect your newborn. It is best to cut back on these drinks especially when you are nearing bedtime.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Regulate their bedroom temperature. Babies sleep better in a cooler room. The optimal temperature for a baby’s room is between 19 and 21 degrees Celsius. If you can’t regulate your child’s room, turn on a fan or open a window slightly. Just make sure the room doesn’t get too cold or too hot.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Don’t make eye contact. When getting up for night time feedings or to sooth them it is best to avoid eye contact. When a baby makes eye contact with you it will cue them to think that it is time to get up.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Do you find your baby is not sleeping?  Did you apply some of these tips successfully or would you like to share your findings with other mums, we like to hear from you.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sweet dreams everyone !</p>", "Baby not sleeping, try these great tips", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "361-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-06-10 04:56:27", "2015-06-10 04:56:27", "", "361", "http://sweetbabylilly.com.au/361-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
